      "span_text": "The comparability of epidemiological and economic estimates between illnesses is also important to inform decisions on the distribution of research effort, as suggested by Leal and colleagues. Japan already has good primary, secondary, and tertiary eye care services as well as good data on the distribution and impact of eye diseases."
